+# D.U.H. Documentation
+
+Welcome to the D.U.H. (Universal Harness) documentation.
+
+[**Architecture Guide**](ARCHITECTURE.md)
+Discover the core structural design of D.U.H. This document explains the top-level module layout, the data flow of a user request, and key extension points for providers and tools. It also covers the threading model and the robust security mechanisms, including taint propagation and confirmation tokens.
+
+[**Tutorial: From Zero to Custom Tool**](TUTORIAL.md)
+A hands-on guide that takes you through the basics of setting up and running D.U.H. locally. You'll learn how to invoke the kernel in stub mode for testing and walk step-by-step through creating, registering, and executing your very own custom tool.
+
+[**API Reference**](API.md)
+A comprehensive index of all public classes and functions within the `duh/kernel/` and `duh/ports/` modules. This reference provides accurate signatures, parameter descriptions, and return types, ensuring you have the precise technical details needed for integration and development.
